This paper discusses the development of text generation technology, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning technology, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (AI) research, making cs.AI another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the advantages and disadvantages of different neural network models, which falls under the category of machine learning (ML), making cs.LG (Learning) a possible sub-category. The paper also discusses the potential for emotional and personalized text generation, which could fall under the category of neural engineering (NE), making cs.NE a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the goal of harmonious human-machine interaction, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (HCI), making cs.HC a possible sub-category.
